Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe Delta police command has paraded three suspects for killing Isaac Odubu and his wife in Amai community.
According to the CP Muhammad Ali, the command acted on intelligence which led to the arrest of three suspects, Chukwudi Sunday, Onyebuchi Paul, Ifeanyi Enuma.
Investigation revealed that the suspects were working for the couple, but decided to go into Internet fraud.
“In their quest for money to buy phones and data, they stormed the house of the couple at night to rob them, during which they killed the couple,” he said on Tuesday.
“Two of the suspects, Chukwudi Sunday and Onyebuchi Paul, raped the wife before she gave up the ghost.
“The suspects will be charged to court upon completion of investigation.”
